description: This file declares the API for the CCSP CWMP Processor component, including functions for creating, removing, enrolling, and initializing the processor object. It serves as the interface for interacting with the CCSP CWMP protocol implementation.

methods.name: CcspCwmpCreateProcessor
methods.description: Creates a new CCSP CWMP Processor object with provided container, owner, and reserved contexts.

methods.name: CcspCwmppoCreate
methods.description: Creates a new instance of the CWMP Processor object.

methods.name: CcspCwmppoRemove
methods.description: Removes and deallocates the given CWMP Processor object instance.

methods.name: CcspCwmppoEnrollObjects
methods.description: Enrolls the necessary objects into the CWMP Processor instance.

methods.name: CcspCwmppoInitialize
methods.description: Initializes the CWMP Processor object after creation.
